The paper discusses the application of a mini-batch based negative sampling method to train a latent factor autoencoder model for collaborative filtering on large scale and sparse data. This involves techniques related to machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
